07:34.680 --> 07:36.610
I didn't know you were here.

07:36.950 --> 07:39.380
Sorry, I scared you. Sorry for screaming.

07:41.150 --> 07:42.659
Did you just get here?

07:42.740 --> 07:45.300
Did you see anyone on the way?

07:45.390 --> 07:46.400
No.

07:46.900 --> 07:50.760
But there's something I must tell you.

07:58.450 --> 08:00.590
Have you checked the automated camera?

08:02.100 --> 08:03.150
Well...

08:03.240 --> 08:06.050
I checked it all, but...

08:35.870 --> 08:39.150
This! What on earth is this?

08:40.740 --> 08:43.890
How can a twig move by itself?

08:45.660 --> 08:48.470
Also, when I was up there,

08:48.550 --> 08:50.490
another branch snapped by itself.

08:50.570 --> 08:53.720
-And it suddenly turned dark,
-Dowon Valley.

08:53.800 --> 08:56.580
and it was so windy.

08:56.660 --> 08:58.420
-I was so scared.
-Dowon Valley, Sumgol Rock.

09:00.020 --> 09:01.030
I'm sorry?

09:01.530 --> 09:02.960
Someone is going to die there.

09:03.550 --> 09:05.190
We need to go there.

09:21.270 --> 09:22.620
Haedong Ranger Station control room.

09:22.700 --> 09:24.880
There's been an SOS report
from Sumgol Rock in Dowon Valley.

09:24.970 --> 09:25.810
I repeat.

09:25.890 --> 09:28.080
There's been an SOS report
from Sumgol Rock in Dowon Valley.

09:28.160 --> 09:29.000
Seseok One.

09:29.080 --> 09:30.550
Bidam One, 1km point from Dowon Valley.

09:30.640 --> 09:32.820
Patrolling the trail
at Sumgol Rock 2km point.

09:32.910 --> 09:34.630
-We'll mobilize.
-We will too.

09:36.220 --> 09:37.480
[How's the victim?]

09:38.160 --> 09:39.540
It must be an urgent situation.

09:39.630 --> 09:42.610
The call ended after he said he was lost.

09:43.410 --> 09:45.510
This is a false report.

09:45.970 --> 09:47.310
Is this okay?

09:53.860 --> 09:55.540
[Haedong Ranger Station control room.]

09:55.750 --> 09:57.640
How does it look? Did you get there?

10:11.760 --> 10:13.230
[We found the victim!]

10:17.090 --> 10:18.310
Take his belt off!

10:19.570 --> 10:20.910
Tilt him more.

10:21.000 --> 10:22.420
The mouth!

10:22.510 --> 10:23.810
Sir.

10:39.520 --> 10:41.200
[National Park]

10:47.790 --> 10:50.020
[Sungjin Hospital]

10:55.310 --> 10:56.360
Yi-gang.

10:56.900 --> 10:58.790
How is he?

10:59.510 --> 11:02.070
It would have been dangerous
if we came any later.

11:02.150 --> 11:03.670
So that's a relief.

11:03.750 --> 11:06.140
He's gotten a lot better
after they washed out his stomach.

11:08.120 --> 11:10.430
What happened to him? Did you ask?

11:11.310 --> 11:14.920
There was something wrong
with the yogurt he drank.

11:16.730 --> 11:18.160
Yogurt drink?

11:18.240 --> 11:21.220
Yes. Someone left a yogurt by the stream.

11:21.310 --> 11:24.460
He was thirsty,
so he didn't think much of it.

11:24.540 --> 11:26.600
And that's when he started to feel sick.

11:27.820 --> 11:28.950
Excuse me!

11:33.440 --> 11:35.170
Where did you get that?

11:35.250 --> 11:37.940
Did you get that from a hiker
or pick it up from somewhere?

11:38.020 --> 11:39.160
Why?

11:39.240 --> 11:41.000
Are we not allowed to
bring this to the mountain?

11:41.090 --> 11:42.310
It's not alcohol.

11:42.390 --> 11:45.370
We can't even drink yogurt here?

11:45.790 --> 11:48.270
Sorry about that. Take care.

11:59.060 --> 12:00.580
What's wrong with you?

12:02.970 --> 12:05.570
Did the police even investigate
Geum-rye's incident?

12:05.660 --> 12:08.300
I told you, it's concluded as an accident.

12:11.660 --> 12:13.470
I met Private Ahn again.

12:13.680 --> 12:17.120
He said the hiker was
closing the rucksack zipper.

12:43.540 --> 12:46.270
He could have put
poison mushrooms in the bag.

12:46.820 --> 12:49.590
To make us think she died
from mushroom poisoning.

12:50.640 --> 12:54.960
But since Private Ahn caught the scene,
he tried to kill him too.

12:55.590 --> 12:56.560
His looks?

12:56.980 --> 12:58.160
Do you remember?

12:58.450 --> 12:59.540
Of course.

13:00.130 --> 13:01.350
He was

13:02.100 --> 13:04.250
about 175cm tall.

13:04.830 --> 13:06.850
Just a regular-looking dude.

13:06.930 --> 13:10.040
In his early thirties, max.

13:11.180 --> 13:13.820
He was wearing a black T-shirt
with white stains

13:14.240 --> 13:16.970
and a pair of beige hiking pants.

13:18.360 --> 13:19.870
We only need to find him.

13:20.750 --> 13:22.520
He's got to be our culprit.

13:22.600 --> 13:24.410
It's all your guess.

13:24.490 --> 13:27.140
You think the police will buy that?

13:32.430 --> 13:35.280
Her family is suffering enough as it is.

13:36.210 --> 13:39.110
We can't burden them more
with something uncertain.

13:43.180 --> 13:44.480
Hello.

13:44.820 --> 13:46.160
Don't get up.

13:46.250 --> 13:47.510
It's all right.

13:47.880 --> 13:50.570
Oh, I can't thank you enough.

13:50.660 --> 13:53.220
Not at all. This is our job.

13:53.300 --> 13:54.640
Still...

13:54.730 --> 13:59.180
I came to ask a couple of things.
Please answer comfortably.

13:59.850 --> 14:02.710
That yogurt...

14:02.790 --> 14:05.230
Where and how did you find it?

14:20.940 --> 14:23.880
Did you see anyone else there?

14:23.960 --> 14:26.520
If there was, I wouldn't be
in this state right now.

14:26.610 --> 14:28.330
There was no one to help me.

14:28.410 --> 14:29.710
My phone stopped working,

14:29.800 --> 14:31.600
and I kept barfing.

14:32.070 --> 14:34.000
I thought I'd die.

14:35.930 --> 14:39.670
I guess the story was true.

14:40.380 --> 14:42.150
About the ghost, you know.

14:42.690 --> 14:43.700
The ghost?

14:43.990 --> 14:46.560
There's a male ghost
on the mountain these days.

14:46.640 --> 14:49.920
And the rumor is you die
in a few after seeing him.

14:50.130 --> 14:52.180
I didn't believe it at first.

14:52.270 --> 14:56.800
But I saw that ghost with my own eyes.

14:57.010 --> 14:58.610
Yes, coming!

14:58.690 --> 15:01.720
[I hid because I thought he was a ranger,]

15:03.940 --> 15:05.790
[but he looked weird.]

15:05.880 --> 15:07.980
He was covered in blood.

15:08.940 --> 15:10.240
A ranger?

15:12.220 --> 15:15.120
That logo on your uniform.

15:15.330 --> 15:18.770
It was on his jumper.

15:18.850 --> 15:22.630
It was white and this long

15:23.050 --> 15:25.200
with that logo on the back.

15:25.990 --> 15:28.560
You mean a snow suit?

15:28.640 --> 15:30.570
I don't know what that is.

15:37.170 --> 15:39.220
You mean this jumper?

15:40.690 --> 15:41.950
It's him.

15:44.010 --> 15:45.060
What do you mean?

15:45.140 --> 15:46.280
It's him!

15:46.360 --> 15:48.590
The ghost I was talking about.

15:49.390 --> 15:50.770
I'm sure of it.

15:51.070 --> 15:52.700
Who is he?

15:52.790 --> 15:54.130
Is he really a ranger?

15:54.220 --> 15:57.070
Why's he covered in blood?

15:58.670 --> 16:00.890
Just because you don't get them
doesn't mean they're lies.

16:00.980 --> 16:01.820
[It gave me a gift.]

16:01.900 --> 16:02.950
To save people.

16:03.040 --> 16:04.000
I saw it.

16:04.090 --> 16:05.260
Where the lost hikers are...

16:05.350 --> 16:06.560
[Kang Hyun-jo.]

16:09.420 --> 16:10.470
Hello?

16:12.190 --> 16:14.920
Yi-gang! It's been so long.

16:15.550 --> 16:16.900
How have you been?

16:17.230 --> 16:20.510
Are you keeping up with rehab training?

16:21.470 --> 16:24.410
[So how can I help you?]

16:26.560 --> 16:27.610
Well...

16:28.490 --> 16:29.830
Hyun-jo...

16:31.180 --> 16:32.690
[How is Hyun-jo?]

16:37.850 --> 16:39.870
He's fine.

16:40.710 --> 16:42.310
[Did he]

16:44.030 --> 16:47.010
regain his consciousness?

16:47.980 --> 16:50.200
No, nothing really happened.

16:51.040 --> 16:53.940
But he's hanging in there.

16:57.510 --> 16:58.850
Okay, thank you.

17:07.589 --> 17:09.230
Yi-gang?

17:10.780 --> 17:13.260
I heard you came back. I guess it's true.

17:13.970 --> 17:16.069
I was worried about you.

17:16.160 --> 17:17.800
I'm glad you look healthy.

17:20.990 --> 17:23.880
Do you need a ride to the ranger station?

17:24.810 --> 17:26.450
No, it's all right.

17:27.290 --> 17:28.710
Okay, then.

17:30.140 --> 17:31.610
You know...

17:33.540 --> 17:35.310
You said before

17:37.320 --> 17:40.640
that anything is possible on the mountain.

17:40.980 --> 17:42.070
Yes.

17:47.070 --> 17:49.290
Could there really be
a ghost on the mountain?

17:49.380 --> 17:52.780
You think all the folktales
set on mountains are false?

17:53.540 --> 17:56.350
You know they call Mount Jirisan
the mountain of patience.

17:56.430 --> 17:58.870
There are more people
who climb with a story or two

17:58.950 --> 18:01.390
than for the sake of leisure.

18:01.470 --> 18:03.870
Those people have sorrow and regret.

18:04.960 --> 18:07.270
And ghosts are all about
sorrow and regret.

18:07.940 --> 18:10.420
If anyone had a strong desire,

18:11.180 --> 18:13.440
they could remain there as a ghost.

18:16.340 --> 18:17.770
Sure.

18:18.860 --> 18:20.790
Then I'll see you around.

18:20.880 --> 18:22.680
[Emergency Ward]

18:37.130 --> 18:39.360
[Year 2018]

18:39.480 --> 18:40.700
[Mud Festival]

18:43.140 --> 18:44.230
[Korea National Park Service]

18:50.740 --> 18:52.170
[Mud Festival, RSVP Now!]

18:55.020 --> 18:56.750
[Name: Jung Gu-yeong]

19:06.660 --> 19:07.960
-What are you up to?
-Goodness!

19:08.040 --> 19:09.050
[Mud Festival]

19:10.020 --> 19:11.110
What?

19:11.820 --> 19:13.750
Girls hate these.

19:13.840 --> 19:16.400
This is exactly why
Yang-sun doesn't like you.

19:16.480 --> 19:17.870
Lee Yang-sun?

19:17.950 --> 19:19.260
Are you two dating?

19:19.340 --> 19:20.940
It's a one-way thing.

19:21.020 --> 19:22.200
It's not!

19:22.280 --> 19:24.170
She's looking at me
differently these days.

19:24.250 --> 19:26.730
She'll think you're a perv
if you try to bring her to this festival.

19:26.820 --> 19:28.160
Is it that bad?

19:28.240 --> 19:29.500
They don't love it.

19:29.590 --> 19:33.070
Their makeup washes off,
and they have to redo it.

19:33.330 --> 19:35.090
How do you know that?
Have you gone with a girl?

19:35.170 --> 19:36.350
Yes.

19:38.870 --> 19:40.210
Then where should I take her?

19:40.970 --> 19:42.900
Why are you asking us?

19:42.990 --> 19:45.040
Ask Yang-sun.

19:47.770 --> 19:50.380
I have to cancel all this?
It took a while.

19:50.460 --> 19:53.610
Will there be half-naked men there?

19:53.700 --> 19:54.750
Yes. Do you want to go?

19:54.830 --> 19:56.590
[Endangered Species Restoration Center]

20:11.670 --> 20:13.140
What is this sound?

20:13.230 --> 20:15.830
What else? It's moon bear.

20:15.960 --> 20:17.590
There are bears here?

20:17.680 --> 20:19.020
Not just bears.

20:19.110 --> 20:20.660
Elks, raccoons, pythons...

20:20.740 --> 20:24.060
They study every animal
and plant from Mount Jirisan.

20:24.150 --> 20:26.670
So why are we here?

20:28.680 --> 20:29.940
Come, you'll see.

20:43.760 --> 20:44.980
Hey.

20:45.400 --> 20:47.880
What did you want to ask?

20:47.960 --> 20:48.970
Who's this?

20:49.050 --> 20:50.060
A newbie?

20:50.520 --> 20:52.490
Hello. I'm Kang Hyun-jo.

20:54.550 --> 20:56.610
You can have some if you want.

20:56.690 --> 20:58.160
Don't. They're for the bears.

20:58.250 --> 21:00.470
My babies are so spoiled.

21:00.560 --> 21:02.410
They won't touch the fruits
if I don't cut them up.

21:02.490 --> 21:04.380
Whatever. Why did you call me?

21:10.260 --> 21:11.560
Is that a Korean rat snake?

21:11.650 --> 21:12.610
That's right.

21:12.700 --> 21:15.170
Because of ecological study
on endangered species,

21:15.260 --> 21:18.320
we injected microchips in ten
and released them.

21:18.410 --> 21:21.640
But number four went missing.

21:21.980 --> 21:23.320
Where is its final location?

21:23.410 --> 21:25.090
Near Bamgol.

21:25.510 --> 21:28.110
But I can't locate the signal
anywhere near there.

21:28.190 --> 21:31.010
I think it went over
to the Haedong Ranger Station side.

21:31.470 --> 21:36.010
Please look for it when you're on patrol.

21:37.520 --> 21:39.240
Here's a tracker.

21:40.120 --> 21:41.340
Hey, Dr. Yoon.

21:42.260 --> 21:44.740
You've worked in the mountain
for years. Don't you get it yet?

21:47.010 --> 21:49.490
You have to look elsewhere,
not the mountain.

21:50.120 --> 21:55.160
[Health Foods]

21:55.370 --> 21:56.590
Welcome.

21:57.800 --> 22:00.370
Are you looking for anything specific?

22:00.700 --> 22:01.630
Are you two married?

22:01.710 --> 22:04.650
Looking to make a baby?

22:04.940 --> 22:06.670
Snakehead is great for women.

22:08.720 --> 22:10.240
Actually...

22:11.790 --> 22:13.930
What's good for virility?

22:14.560 --> 22:16.070
You've come to the right place.

22:17.000 --> 22:18.170
How about turtle soup?

22:18.260 --> 22:20.650
We make good turtle soup.

22:20.860 --> 22:23.890
No, you know what I mean.

22:23.970 --> 22:26.030
Something that really works.

22:26.280 --> 22:27.540
Like...

22:30.190 --> 22:32.330
snake, you know?

22:44.970 --> 22:46.440
Are you sure that's the one?

22:46.520 --> 22:47.530
Yes.

22:47.610 --> 22:50.390
If it disappeared near Bamgol,
it must be around here.

22:50.470 --> 22:52.910
And I heard that store
is making a bank lately.

22:52.990 --> 22:54.330
I'm sure that's the one.

22:55.220 --> 22:57.360
I don't know about this.

22:57.440 --> 22:59.540
If it's within 700m,
the tracker should go off.

22:59.630 --> 23:01.350
But there's no signal.

23:01.940 --> 23:03.620
You just wait.

23:03.700 --> 23:05.210
They'll make a move soon.

23:06.770 --> 23:10.000
I heard you study mushrooms there too.

23:10.080 --> 23:13.990
Do you study Common Rustgill too?

23:14.830 --> 23:16.640
It's a dangerous mushroom.

23:16.720 --> 23:18.150
Of course we do.

23:19.200 --> 23:21.340
Can a regular person

23:21.420 --> 23:23.230
extract poison from it?

23:23.570 --> 23:25.790
I doubt it.

23:25.880 --> 23:28.190
You need proper tools to do it.

23:28.400 --> 23:30.450
Why do you ask?

23:31.250 --> 23:32.680
This is his guess,

23:32.760 --> 23:37.130
but someone's putting the poison
in yogurt to kill people.

23:37.220 --> 23:38.850
Seriously? Who? Why?

23:38.940 --> 23:40.450
I said it's his guess.

23:41.000 --> 23:42.470
Do you think that's possible?

23:43.260 --> 23:46.040
It's not impossible.

23:46.670 --> 23:49.610
Someone who knows an extraction method

23:49.980 --> 23:53.640
and the geography or vegetation
of Mount Jirisan could do it.

23:54.100 --> 23:56.490
But that's only rangers...

23:57.000 --> 23:59.850
Why would a national park ranger

23:59.940 --> 24:01.580
do such a thing?

24:04.430 --> 24:06.200
Hold on. Look!

24:07.040 --> 24:09.180
[Health Foods]

24:09.350 --> 24:10.230
Hey.

24:10.900 --> 24:11.910
Take this.

24:12.030 --> 24:13.170
Hide, hide now.

24:13.250 --> 24:14.090
Quick! Follow them!

24:14.180 --> 24:16.400
Seat belts!
I need to put on the seat belt.

24:16.490 --> 24:17.750
Why isn't it starting?

24:48.610 --> 24:51.430
You're too close. They'll find out.

24:57.140 --> 24:59.320
We're getting a signal!

25:34.730 --> 25:36.700
Why aren't they coming out?

25:37.920 --> 25:39.430
Should we go in?

25:40.150 --> 25:41.660
Wait.

25:42.330 --> 25:43.840
Should we call the police first?

25:44.350 --> 25:45.610
Yi-gang!

25:46.490 --> 25:47.790
Yi-gang!

25:52.660 --> 25:54.180
Freeze!

25:55.440 --> 25:56.570
Yi-gang!

26:20.470 --> 26:22.520
Who do you think you are?

26:22.610 --> 26:24.200
Do you own that mountain?

26:24.830 --> 26:28.450
Don't you know the law
regarding wild animal protection?

26:29.200 --> 26:31.090
Look! Here.

26:31.680 --> 26:35.540
"If you process, distribute, or store
wild animals in danger of extinction,"

26:35.630 --> 26:40.210
"you'll be imprisoned for 2 years
or charged with a fine of 20 million won."

26:40.290 --> 26:42.600
What do you know, kid?

26:42.680 --> 26:45.880
My family's been collecting herbs
and catching animals on that mountain

26:45.960 --> 26:47.850
since my grandfather's grandfather.

26:49.820 --> 26:51.670
You must be real proud.

26:51.760 --> 26:54.150
-What? Come here!
-Stop it.

26:54.230 --> 26:56.710
-Darn you!
-I'm here!

26:56.800 --> 26:58.350
What are you going to do?

26:58.430 --> 26:59.820
-What can you do?
-Stop it.

27:00.450 --> 27:02.050
National Park, my foot!

27:02.130 --> 27:04.690
Humans came before mountains!

27:05.360 --> 27:07.460
Is that why you caught so many snakes?

27:07.550 --> 27:09.900
You could've wiped out the whole species!

27:09.980 --> 27:12.460
-You look like a snake!
-What did you say?

27:12.550 --> 27:16.200
What have those poor snakes
ever done to you?

27:16.280 --> 27:18.760
I should have known when you winked at me.

27:18.970 --> 27:21.830
-Hey! Who do you think you are?
-How dare you kill all those snakes?

27:21.910 --> 27:23.720
-Why mess with me?
-What did you say?

27:24.770 --> 27:27.370
-Get off of me!
-What?

27:27.460 --> 27:28.970
-Darn it!
-Come at me!

27:38.840 --> 27:40.100
Is that the newbie?

27:40.690 --> 27:41.900
Yes.

27:43.420 --> 27:46.610
He's tall but very plain-looking.

27:47.450 --> 27:48.920
I wouldn't say he is plain.

27:49.250 --> 27:50.930
He's not normal, though.

27:53.330 --> 27:54.920
Is that so?

27:56.730 --> 27:58.830
What a shame. He's so young though.

28:07.560 --> 28:10.340
23 black and 18 yellow rat snakes,

28:10.420 --> 28:13.530
and 53 tiger keelbacks.
That's 94 in total.

28:16.850 --> 28:18.270
Well done.

28:19.580 --> 28:20.790
Thanks a lot.

28:22.600 --> 28:23.520
Good night.

28:24.950 --> 28:26.170
Oh, right.

28:28.940 --> 28:30.500
We should head back now.

28:31.710 --> 28:32.760
Okay.

29:34.840 --> 29:39.160
This trail is a lot worse
than other restricted areas.

29:39.250 --> 29:41.140
Not even herb collectors come here.

29:41.220 --> 29:43.830
And since there are no humans,
it's animal paradise.

29:58.020 --> 29:59.320
And...

29:59.910 --> 30:03.860
This is the only graveyard
where you can see Cheonwangbong Peak.

30:25.200 --> 30:26.460
Is this it?

30:27.420 --> 30:29.020
Yes, it is.

30:51.990 --> 30:53.460
Nothing, right?

30:55.520 --> 30:57.750
Yes, I guess.

30:58.420 --> 30:59.760
Let's go down.

31:00.520 --> 31:02.160
We've got special patrol to do.

31:09.760 --> 31:12.030
How come you came with me
without a question?

31:12.490 --> 31:15.260
You always yell at me for saying nonsense.

31:15.470 --> 31:17.820
But today, you came without a complaint.

31:17.900 --> 31:19.160
It's weird. You're Demon Seo.

31:20.470 --> 31:22.610
You don't want to live long, do you?

31:35.920 --> 31:38.780
Darn it. Who do they think they are?

31:39.830 --> 31:41.420
Hurry up before it gets dark.

31:42.180 --> 31:44.950
What if we get caught again?

31:45.160 --> 31:46.720
How else will we pay the fine?

31:46.800 --> 31:48.520
Are we going to starve the kids?

31:49.070 --> 31:51.170
It's either do or die.

31:55.580 --> 31:57.850
What are you doing? You go that way.

32:20.690 --> 32:23.510
How could such a graveyard
still remain in a national park?

32:23.590 --> 32:26.490
Aren't illegal properties
subject to demolition here?

32:26.570 --> 32:29.300
For the graves that were here
before it became a national park,

32:29.390 --> 32:31.700
families often don't agree to move them.

32:31.780 --> 32:32.960
Like that one.

32:34.050 --> 32:37.620
Chuseok is over,
and Cold Food festival is not here yet.

32:37.960 --> 32:41.020
No one will come for a while,
which means no injuries.

32:41.110 --> 32:42.870
Not only families come here.

32:42.950 --> 32:45.390
[There are many animals around too.]

32:45.890 --> 32:50.770
[Especially snakes are spotted
a lot under a stone table.]

33:38.560 --> 33:41.040
Haedong One, 3km from Saemagol.
An explosion noise!

33:41.120 --> 33:42.550
Check for an SOS report!

34:23.630 --> 34:24.929
Don't come up!

34:25.010 --> 34:26.150
Stay there!

35:11.250 --> 35:12.510
A potato bomb?

35:13.310 --> 35:14.400
That's right.

35:14.490 --> 35:19.650
Homemade bombs used by poachers
who hunted moon bears in the 60s and 70s.

35:19.990 --> 35:23.980
Bear liver and gall bladder
were considered a luxury back then.

35:24.190 --> 35:27.090
So the poachers set them up
here and there on Mount Jirisan.

35:27.250 --> 35:30.070
It's kind of like a landmine.

35:30.870 --> 35:32.970
But they're still on the mountain?

35:33.050 --> 35:35.440
In the 60s, when the national park
was established,

35:35.530 --> 35:37.590
everyone including the villagers searched

35:37.670 --> 35:39.520
and removed any remaining bombs.

35:39.600 --> 35:42.460
But they couldn't reach
the deep restricted trails.

35:43.930 --> 35:45.360
This is Mount Jirisan, after all.

35:45.650 --> 35:48.800
But how did this old junk explode?

35:48.880 --> 35:51.780
The casing of a potato bomb
is entirely sealed with wax.

35:51.870 --> 35:53.460
And because no wind or rain could get in,

35:53.550 --> 35:55.940
the detonator and explosive
must have remained inside.

35:58.080 --> 36:00.980
We keep telling them not to enter.

36:04.590 --> 36:05.940
Well...

36:06.270 --> 36:07.950
I have something to tell you.

36:10.050 --> 36:13.450
We patrolled the site before the accident.

36:15.680 --> 36:19.750
We've looked all around
for any dangerous objects.

36:20.510 --> 36:23.790
But the bomb wasn't there.

36:24.460 --> 36:25.550
Is that true?

36:29.330 --> 36:30.340
Yes.

36:30.420 --> 36:32.020
Did you really look everywhere?

36:32.100 --> 36:34.370
Maybe you confused it with something else.

36:34.450 --> 36:35.420
No.

36:36.050 --> 36:37.940
There really was nothing then.

36:38.020 --> 36:39.110
I'm positive.

36:39.700 --> 36:41.260
Are you sure?

36:45.460 --> 36:47.890
If you're not sure,
this is a huge problem.

36:47.980 --> 36:51.500
It means a civilian died
because of a park ranger's mistake.

37:04.650 --> 37:07.670
My goodness.

37:08.430 --> 37:12.250
Take me with you.

37:14.520 --> 37:16.450
How could you leave me?

37:16.540 --> 37:19.730
What on earth is wrong with you all?

37:20.270 --> 37:23.470
You act like you own the mountain,

37:23.840 --> 37:27.290
and look what you've done to my husband!

37:31.530 --> 37:32.660
Please calm down, and let's...

37:32.750 --> 37:35.690
How can you say that?
My husband died before my eyes!

37:36.110 --> 37:37.410
Bring him back.

37:37.750 --> 37:39.130
Bring him back!

37:39.220 --> 37:41.020
Bring my husband back!

37:41.480 --> 37:46.440
We're terribly sorry about the accident.

37:46.900 --> 37:48.080
Accident?

37:48.540 --> 37:49.880
Did you say it was an accident?

37:50.640 --> 37:51.690
I saw

37:52.110 --> 37:56.310
those two on the mountain that day.

37:56.810 --> 37:58.830
Yet, they did nothing!

37:58.910 --> 37:59.840
Am I wrong?

37:59.920 --> 38:04.330
They just let the bomb explode!

38:05.210 --> 38:08.280
The reason he went
to the mountain that day

38:09.670 --> 38:11.550
is because of you all.

38:11.890 --> 38:17.520
He needed to make money somehow
after getting all the snakes taken!

38:17.600 --> 38:18.860
You have

38:21.930 --> 38:24.110
murdered my husband!

38:28.980 --> 38:33.020
-Mom...
-I can't let him go like this!

38:34.650 --> 38:36.960
Please get a grip!

38:37.130 --> 38:40.790
I won't move a step
until you pay for his life!

38:41.670 --> 38:46.620
I'll stay here with my husband!

38:46.710 --> 38:48.300
Calm down.

38:48.470 --> 38:50.320
Bring him back!

38:52.340 --> 38:54.100
My poor son.

38:55.740 --> 38:58.050
Bring him back!

38:59.600 --> 39:02.160
My poor son.

39:03.930 --> 39:05.650
My goodness.

39:15.940 --> 39:18.040
[Health Foods]

39:30.140 --> 39:33.410
[Jirisan National Park Jeonbuk Office]

39:33.500 --> 39:36.310
[Jirisan National Park
Haedong Ranger Station]

39:39.380 --> 39:41.010
["Coffin Can't Leave. Whose Fault Is It?"]

39:41.100 --> 39:44.290
["Bad Maintenance of National Park
Loses a Man's Life"]

39:46.050 --> 39:48.410
It's been days already.

39:48.660 --> 39:50.300
We must come up with measures.

39:50.380 --> 39:51.220
Yes.

39:51.300 --> 39:53.610
It's still hot during the day.

39:53.700 --> 39:57.900
If the corpse starts to rot,
the media will get even louder.

39:57.980 --> 40:01.510
Why don't we compensate them now?

40:03.230 --> 40:04.570
That's impossible.

40:05.710 --> 40:08.020
What happened is unfortunate,

40:08.230 --> 40:11.380
but it happened in a restricted area.

40:11.460 --> 40:13.060
If we compensate them,

40:13.140 --> 40:17.470
the grounds for regulating
illegal hikers will get weaker.

40:17.800 --> 40:19.610
Well, we can't leave them like that.

40:19.690 --> 40:22.000
We must take responsibility somehow.

40:22.090 --> 40:23.100
[Chief of Korea National Park Service]

40:23.470 --> 40:24.610
You're right.

40:27.550 --> 40:28.810
Someone

40:30.610 --> 40:32.040
must take responsibility.

40:33.850 --> 40:35.070
Seo Yi-gang.

40:35.530 --> 40:37.840
Is it true that you were there
before the accident?

40:38.300 --> 40:42.710
You could've recognized
and removed such a dangerous thing.

40:42.790 --> 40:44.640
What's wrong with Haedong Station lately?

40:45.940 --> 40:48.460
Hey, have you seen a potato bomb?

40:48.840 --> 40:52.750
How can you remove something
you don't know?

40:52.830 --> 40:54.180
That's not all.

40:54.640 --> 40:57.870
Last time with Geum-rye, too.
Why are there so many accidents?

41:03.210 --> 41:05.350
I'll say this as a team leader.

41:06.150 --> 41:07.700
Stay vigilant.

41:07.780 --> 41:10.050
That stupid team leader nonsense.

41:10.140 --> 41:12.570
You should have become a team leader then.

41:22.270 --> 41:24.040
How did it go?

41:24.120 --> 41:25.800
What did the chief say?

41:26.220 --> 41:30.130
He'll take the responsibility and resign.

41:39.700 --> 41:40.710
Sir!

41:42.350 --> 41:43.690
What Hyun-jo told is the truth.

41:43.780 --> 41:46.930
There was nothing there
when we were on patrol.

41:47.350 --> 41:49.910
Someone placed it there
after we did our patrol.

41:50.120 --> 41:51.290
If we find the person,

41:51.710 --> 41:53.810
we'll prove that it wasn't our fault.

41:53.900 --> 41:54.740
All right.

41:54.820 --> 41:57.640
Let's say that someone did.

41:58.390 --> 42:01.750
Then finding that person
is the police's job.

42:02.000 --> 42:03.050
But...

42:03.140 --> 42:04.650
We have our own job.

42:05.870 --> 42:07.840
It's to protect those
who come to the mountain.

42:10.660 --> 42:13.050
Local residents are the ones
who come here the most.

42:13.890 --> 42:15.860
Our priority

42:16.490 --> 42:17.960
is to regain their trust.

42:20.950 --> 42:22.160
See you around.

42:54.250 --> 42:55.600
Bring him back!

42:56.440 --> 42:58.620
Bring him back!

43:02.860 --> 43:05.420
Bring my husband back.

43:06.390 --> 43:08.490
Please bring my husband back

43:10.930 --> 43:12.520
Bring him back.

43:14.120 --> 43:16.180
How am I going to live without him?

43:18.150 --> 43:20.040
Bring him back!

43:26.510 --> 43:29.070
[Jirisan National Park
Haedong Ranger Station]

43:38.690 --> 43:40.700
My poor son...

43:54.350 --> 43:56.540
Dad.

43:57.630 --> 43:59.140
Dad!

44:01.490 --> 44:06.450
-Dad.
-My poor son...

44:13.800 --> 44:15.180
Let's go back.

44:18.170 --> 44:19.970
I can't end it like this.

44:21.780 --> 44:23.420
Don't make matters worse.

44:23.920 --> 44:26.820
Chief resigned,
trying so hard to settle this down.

44:29.420 --> 44:30.810
I saw a hand.

44:32.530 --> 44:34.590
[There were five scratch scars]

44:35.050 --> 44:37.360
[like from a small animal's claws.]

44:38.120 --> 44:39.460
I can never

44:40.760 --> 44:42.190
forget that hand.

44:44.120 --> 44:45.420
Enough.

44:49.370 --> 44:50.590
On that day,

44:52.270 --> 44:55.250
someone else was on that mountain.

44:58.700 --> 45:00.380
I will find that person,

45:02.140 --> 45:03.610
no matter what it takes.

45:21.500 --> 45:25.200
[If you find this explosive,
do not touch it]

45:25.280 --> 45:29.190
[and report immediately
to the national park office.]

45:29.610 --> 45:31.960
[Caution, Explosion Risk]

45:37.670 --> 45:39.220
[Caution, Explosion Risk]

45:58.800 --> 45:59.890
Who's there?

46:14.460 --> 46:15.850
What brings you here?

46:16.140 --> 46:18.410
I have something to ask you.

46:18.790 --> 46:21.770
Okay. I'll be done in a second.

46:25.130 --> 46:26.980
They're all found on Mount Jirisan.

46:28.150 --> 46:30.170
You know, to capture wild animals

46:30.510 --> 46:32.400
like bears, raccoons, snakes, and badgers.

46:33.490 --> 46:35.420
Although this time,
a person was sacrificed.

46:41.640 --> 46:45.370
[Town Hall Meeting,
Information Session on Explosives]

46:45.500 --> 46:46.760
Darn it.

46:47.430 --> 46:49.490
It's so busy today.

46:49.620 --> 46:52.600
Why did the newbie have to be sick today?

46:53.310 --> 46:55.030
That's strange.

46:55.120 --> 46:56.960
Where did this sick kid go
in this early morning?

46:57.050 --> 46:58.180
He wasn't in the residence.

46:58.270 --> 46:59.110
No?

46:59.190 --> 47:00.620
He must be really sick.

47:00.950 --> 47:04.570
He called me early, saying he'll
get checked at a big hospital.

47:04.730 --> 47:05.620
What?

47:06.290 --> 47:07.210
Really?

47:07.510 --> 47:08.980
What's wrong with him?

47:12.000 --> 47:13.260
His head.

47:13.930 --> 47:15.020
Head?

47:20.990 --> 47:22.040
Head?

47:22.250 --> 47:23.300
Hey.

47:23.760 --> 47:25.940
We don't have enough drinks.
Go get some more.

47:26.780 --> 47:27.670
Okay.

47:27.750 --> 47:29.470
No, no. I'll go.

47:29.560 --> 47:31.870
Help me, Yang-sun. Come with me.

47:31.950 --> 47:34.340
Why's everyone so awkward today?

47:34.430 --> 47:35.690
No, just hurry.

47:37.370 --> 47:39.300
Why are they going together?

47:39.380 --> 47:40.640
The potato bomb?

47:41.110 --> 47:42.200
Yes.

47:42.370 --> 47:45.980
I heard that you've been
researching on it.

47:47.200 --> 47:48.460
Was it

47:48.830 --> 47:51.980
really the one the poachers
used in the 1960s?

47:53.120 --> 47:54.500
Could someone have

47:54.590 --> 47:58.410
copied one from the past?

47:58.830 --> 47:59.960
No.

48:00.340 --> 48:03.580
You can't get any parts
of the bomb from anywhere now.

48:03.660 --> 48:06.810
I'm certain it was
what the poachers used in the past.

48:13.660 --> 48:15.210
You said

48:15.550 --> 48:18.320
they removed a bunch of
potato bombs before.

48:18.700 --> 48:21.720
Were the bombs sent anywhere?

48:23.270 --> 48:26.590
Like a museum or a national park.

48:26.890 --> 48:29.620
Why would the park keep
such a dangerous thing?

48:30.370 --> 48:33.270
They were dismantled
and burned immediately.

48:34.740 --> 48:36.500
I see.

48:37.050 --> 48:39.820
Why do you ask?

48:41.330 --> 48:43.850
Do you think it wasn't an accident?

48:47.880 --> 48:49.060
Yes.

48:49.310 --> 48:51.750
That's very unlikely.

48:52.000 --> 48:54.520
I mean, there were some people in the town

48:54.600 --> 48:58.380
who found them on their own
and kept them privately,

48:58.680 --> 49:01.320
but I heard they were all confiscated.

49:02.460 --> 49:04.560
Privately owned bombs?

49:04.770 --> 49:05.940
By who?

49:06.280 --> 49:10.610
Some workers kept them as a souvenir.

49:11.030 --> 49:13.920
Could I get a list of them?

49:15.100 --> 49:16.990
I told you.

49:18.250 --> 49:20.060
It's highly unlikely.

49:20.640 --> 49:21.860
That's okay.

49:27.830 --> 49:29.510
[We don't have a list,]

49:30.050 --> 49:33.920
[but I can introduce you to
one of the workers from then.]

49:34.380 --> 49:39.960
[He'll probably know other workers.]

50:04.790 --> 50:05.960
I'll take this too.

50:06.050 --> 50:07.430
-No, it's fine.
-Don't worry.

50:07.520 --> 50:10.160
I've been working out,
so my arms feel strong.

50:10.250 --> 50:12.510
Boy, these are light as a feather!

50:16.170 --> 50:17.600
Oh, not this one!

50:24.100 --> 50:27.040
You must be tired because of all this.

50:27.720 --> 50:30.190
How did that stupid potato bomb...

50:30.280 --> 50:31.500
Who's there?

50:34.440 --> 50:36.410
get left behind?

50:44.310 --> 50:45.940
Don't worry, though.

50:46.740 --> 50:48.420
It won't happen again.

50:49.050 --> 50:51.740
This is when you need
a change of surroundings.

50:51.820 --> 50:54.720
You want to go for a drive
on your day off?

50:55.140 --> 50:57.490
There's this Milking Goats Festival.

50:57.580 --> 50:59.130
It's supposed to be really fun.

51:00.810 --> 51:04.760
Do you want to go milk some goats with me?

51:06.650 --> 51:09.970
I'm sorry, but I need to
go to the station right now.

51:10.050 --> 51:11.060
Sorry.

51:13.240 --> 51:14.550
Okay.

51:20.760 --> 51:22.230
I got dumped again.

51:23.790 --> 51:25.760
What on earth is the problem?

52:02.220 --> 52:03.350
Hello?

52:06.330 --> 52:07.840
Anyone there?

52:15.990 --> 52:17.040
Who is it?

52:17.120 --> 52:18.090
Hello.

52:18.170 --> 52:19.520
I'm from the national park.

52:20.990 --> 52:22.420
The national park?

52:22.840 --> 52:25.860
Mr. Kang at the Restoration Center
referred me here.

52:26.030 --> 52:29.640
I heard you were a part of
the bomb removal process.

52:29.810 --> 52:31.400
Yes, so?

52:31.490 --> 52:35.060
I have something to ask
about the potato bombs.

52:45.680 --> 52:48.200
I don't know anything.

52:48.370 --> 52:49.340
One second!

52:50.050 --> 52:51.900
I know you've got nothing to do with this.

52:51.980 --> 52:54.040
I'm only asking to check.

52:55.510 --> 52:58.450
Is there anything that you know
about the recent bomb incident?

52:59.040 --> 53:01.810
I know nothing!

53:01.900 --> 53:04.420
The bomb just disappeared!

53:05.720 --> 53:07.230
The bomb disappeared?

53:09.920 --> 53:12.400
I swear I left it in here.

53:12.480 --> 53:15.380
But it just disappeared.

53:15.710 --> 53:18.400
I didn't want people to get the wrong idea
so I didn't share it.

53:19.540 --> 53:21.550
So pretend you didn't see this.

53:22.140 --> 53:24.410
I don't want to get my granddaughter
in trouble.

53:26.420 --> 53:27.680
Your granddaughter?

53:30.330 --> 53:31.460
Hello.

53:31.550 --> 53:32.980
Where are the people?

53:33.060 --> 53:34.700
They should be here soon.

53:35.750 --> 53:37.430
Oh, granny is here.

53:37.760 --> 53:38.980
Hello!

53:41.710 --> 53:43.060
Thank you for your hard work.

53:43.310 --> 53:44.360
Welcome.

53:49.350 --> 53:52.420
Girl, you haven't called in days!

53:53.680 --> 53:55.440
Have you been skipping your meals?

53:55.530 --> 53:58.850
It's not just me. We've all been busy.

54:00.480 --> 54:01.950
Are you okay?

54:05.270 --> 54:08.090
Did you come alone? What about others?

54:08.170 --> 54:10.520
They said they'd come.

54:10.730 --> 54:12.710
Oh, there they are.

54:20.520 --> 54:22.070
Thank you for coming.

54:22.160 --> 54:24.130
I'm not here to forgive you.

54:24.210 --> 54:26.270
I want to watch what you all have to say.

54:29.460 --> 54:33.870
Let's go in first.

54:34.760 --> 54:36.520
Come in.

54:53.400 --> 54:55.500
[Haedong Town Hall]

55:05.330 --> 55:06.720
[Information Session on Explosives]

56:07.320 --> 56:09.040
If her work finds out about this,

56:09.340 --> 56:11.940
she might get in trouble.

56:13.370 --> 56:15.050
You're her colleague.

56:15.470 --> 56:19.210
So please just let it pass.

56:46.380 --> 56:47.850
[I saw a hand.]

56:50.250 --> 56:52.430
[There were five scratch scars]

56:53.310 --> 56:55.750
[like from a small animal's claws.]

